gomodel:SYNGO_1448  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Electrophysiological characterisation of BK beta4 subunits overexposed in Oocytes with patch-clamp.\n\nrule: NAS_MFCC-BP\nrationale:\nProtein has voltage-gated ion channel activity and is localized in the presynaptic membrane (show with high-resolution technique). The inference to term 'voltage-gated ion channel activity involved in regulation of presynaptic membrane potential (GO:0099508)' is trivial and non-controversial.\nPinf_CC:\n[Q9ESK8] SyNGO ID 1447 (PMID:19321803, EM). Experimental description: The rb4 and the rat BKCa channel a-subunit (rSlo) cDNAs were subcloned into pGH vector for expression in Xenopus oocytes." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9425-2935" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_1448" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

